subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis
. This species differs from other species of the genus by the following character states: 
1
) clypeus separated from face by a distinct transverse groove, 
2
) occipital carina complete, 
3
) tarsus mostly dark, apical tarsal segments slightly enlarged, 
4
) apical lateral fields of propodeum absent, 
5
) last visible metasomal tergite not modified, 
6
) ovipositor straight.
